title: Alzheimer 's in the U.S : lifetime risks , by age and gender
summary: This grouped bar chart represents 2 different Countrys on X-axis for 2 groups Men, and Women. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding SOME LABEL.
Out of all 2 groups, Women had the highest SOME LABEL in Country 65 years and Men had the lowest SOME LABEL in Country 45 years.
In Country 65 years, Women had the maximum SOME LABEL and it saw the lowest in Country 45 years out of all 2 Countrys.
Country 65 years and 45 years had the biggest gap of 95.0 between the highest and lowest SOME LABEL found for Women.
